    "spellcaster": false,
    "monster": true,
    "notes": "400kg Beast (Killer), mountain flyer, #App: 1d6, Treasure: Incidental. Teeth (3d6), claws (2d6); armor 6; fly 30m/action; Morale +0. Often mistakenly called a \"dragon\" by villagers, the drake is a non-sentient relative of true dragons. It is still capable of breathing fire. A few young knights have made their names bragging about slaying a dragon, when they only killed a drake. 3 times a day may breathe fire, causing 3d6 fire damage to all within a 10m long, 5m wide cone emanating from its mouth. Victims may throw DEX 8+ to only suffer half damage (rounded down). A drake's fire has an AV 2d6 rating vs. vehicles and may set them ablaze as described in the Combat chapter.",
